The City of Cape Town’s Fire and Rescue Service station commander, Theo Layne, said a large area of vegetation was affected by the blaze on the mountain slopes. “Four fire engines, three water tankers with 37 firefighters were at the scene of the fire. Table Mountain National Parks was also on the scene to assist the Fire and Rescue Department. “The roadway was closed from Kloof Nek Road at the circle and one  contracted helicopter was in use,” said Layne. He said no injuries were reported and hikers in the Platte-klip Gorge area were evacuated  for safety purposes. Firefighters were still on the scene late Sunday “dealing with numerous hotspots breaking out,” according to Layne. Cape Argus